        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:57PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms along a line
extending from near Golva to 16 miles southwest of Mud Buttes.
Movement was northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sunset Butte, Fryburg, Bowman, Mud Buttes, Buffalo Springs, Three V
Crossing, Pretty Butte, Medora, Beach, Golva, Sentinel Butte, Rhame,
Alpha, Sentinel Butte State Nature Preserve, Marmarth, Griffin, Sully
Creek State Park, and Amidon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
